âœ… Launch browser â†’ Open URL â†’ Maximize window

2ï¸âƒ£ @BeforeMethod (from MyInfoPageTest)
âœ… Set up PageFactory â†’ Login as Admin â†’ Load personal details data

3ï¸âƒ£ @Test (test01_verifyPersonalDetailsOnMyInfoPage)
âœ… Navigate to My Info â†’ Click Job Option â†’ Assert Job Details

4ï¸âƒ£ @AfterMethod (from UIBaseTest)
âœ… Quit the browser â†’ Clean up the driver

========================================

ğŸ”¹ How This Works for Multiple Test Cases?
TestNG runs each test method independently, meaning that the full lifecycle (@BeforeMethod â†’ @Test â†’ @AfterMethod) repeats for each test case.
If you run two test cases, the execution will be:

1ï¸âƒ£ @BeforeMethod (UIBaseTest)
2ï¸âƒ£ @BeforeMethod (MyInfoPageTest)
3ï¸âƒ£ @Test â†’ test01_verifyPersonalDetailsOnMyInfoPage
4ï¸âƒ£ @AfterMethod (UIBaseTest)

5ï¸âƒ£ @BeforeMethod (UIBaseTest)
6ï¸âƒ£ @BeforeMethod (MyInfoPageTest)
7ï¸âƒ£ @Test â†’ test02_verifyUserIsAbleToFillPersonalDetails
8ï¸âƒ£ @AfterMethod (UIBaseTest)

===========================================================================
ğŸ”¹ Key Takeaways
âœ… Each test method runs in isolation.
âœ… Parent @BeforeMethod runs before child @BeforeMethod.
âœ… Parent @AfterMethod runs after each test method.
âœ… WebDriver is initialized and closed for each test execution, ensuring clean browser sessions.

